body: CC @dbczumar I think this is by design. We export `MlflowClient` to `mlflow` module now.

@WeichenXu123 The issue is https://mlflow.org/docs/latest/python_api/mlflow.tracking.html#mlflow.tracking.MlflowClient.get_latest_versions used to be available but it's not now because we changed the module structure.
@amesar As a workaround, you can go to this link to see 1.27 version document. https://mlflow.org/docs/1.27.0/python_api/mlflow.tracking.html
We can try this sphinx plugin https://documatt.gitlab.io/sphinx-reredirects/usage.html to add redirecting instructions.

@WeichenXu123 But that still requires me (and all others) to edit every document or web page and make change. Why can't our webserver do  a 301 redirect? Pretty standard procedure to prevent broken links. ;)
The old `mlflow.tracking.html.MlflowClient` works in Python code, so should the links too. From a doc perspective, this is a breaking change.

https://mlflow.org is hosted on S3. To redirect https://mlflow.org/docs/latest/python_api/mlflow.client.html to https://mlflow.org/docs/latest/python_api/mlflow.tracking.html, we can apply https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AmazonS3/latest/userguide/how-to-page-redirect.html#redirect-requests-object-metadata, but this requires both `mlflow.client.html` and `mlflow.tracking.html` exist.

Breaking changes in docs are permissible. The issue here is that our Algolia index of pages appears not to have been updated; the root cause is unclear. Updating the index so that searches for MlflowClient yield results in the mlflow.client module is the correct solution. I'm looking into it but would appreciate help from others on this thread as well.

@dbczumar I'm not sure if this config file is still valid: https://github.com/algolia/docsearch-configs/blob/master/deployed-configs/m/mlflow.js, but the crawler for `mlflow` is scheduled to run at `at 10:20 on Thursday`. If we updated the docs after 10:20 last Thursday (August 11th), we might need to wait a few more days.
`mlflow.pipelines` (added in 1.27.0) matches nothing. I think something is wrong with the crawler.
